      <h2>Great music deserves great art.</h2>
      <p>I co-founded, creative directed, and ultimately closed a design agency in the music industry from 2014 to the end of 2016. Mocktail completed about 45 client engagements and was comprised of five talented artists and designers during its lifetime.</p>
      <h3>The End of Art and the Rise of Producerism</h3>
      <p>The forward to Mocktail’s story is <a href="https://www.theatlantic.com/magazine/archive/2015/01/the-death-of-the-artist-and-the-birth-of-the-creative-entrepreneur/383497/">William Deresiewicz’s lucid 2015 dissection of creative industry in The Atlantic.</a> Although we were running Mocktail before the time of publication, Deresiewicz perfectly captures the context and sets the scene for our story.</p>
      <p>TL;DR: Art is dead. Craft is king. Producerism is the new consumerism. Enter, Mocktail.</p>
